Cook, Art,<br><br>
You mentioned this sight and the effect it has had on you.  I feared this site when it started because I didn't know what I would find inside.  Some of those fears have been justified.<br><br>
I am beginning to learn why I should feel more and what I have been missing.  I love solitude, at the expense of other important things.  As a protective mechanism I try to be outward and sometimes too talkative because I don't have a natural control.  I am with people and my mind is screaming for solitude so I force myself.<br><br>
I am having mood swings now that I didn't have before.  My family has noticed this and asked me why.  I was always my stern controlled self.  New experience and I have no practice in making it work.  I am much more comfortable in the no feelings niche.<br><br>
Funny, although I do not feel those normal emotions others feel, death means nothing to me.  I swell with pride at a job well done and boil over with enthusiasm when the kids do well.  I do not have to fake that at all.<br><br>
I also hold back.  No pictures on the wall or the desk.  No one knows my complete background.  I don't talk about the military or other defense jobs except with one of the kindred.  Nothing in common I presume.  I have a lot of acquaintances who know nothing of my past.  Call few people friends.  The word to me is something not used easily.  A friend is someone with whom I can trust my life.<br><br>
I wonder if Doc Spatz in all his years as a Shrink hasn't carried some of the baggage home.  The Shrinks I have known are impacted by the constant exposure.  They become non feeling or inherit others conditions.  You can't have empathy for everybody and not pay a price.  Maybe Doc should come clean and let us know these things.<br><br>
I have needed this group to gain my identity.  I learned to hide my past because of all the intrusive questions and the open hostility.  The rage from the insults boiled but most didn't know I was the target.<br><br>
I think your correct Cook.  Same Same Me.  We are effected, but have become comfortable.  Our definition of normal has shifted.  Art is wise in his statement about not looking too deep because demons reside there.  If we have a sense of equilibrium we can't let comments from Doc or anyone else change things.  Too high a price to pay.  True if it ain't broke, don't fix it.  To thine own self be true.<br><br>
My Thoughts<br><br>
SW<br>

